\section{Time formatting}

We need to format ISO timestamps for Canvas API calls and display.
The [[format_canvas_time()]] function is provided by the [[utils]] module and
is used throughout the calendar module for consistent time handling.

It parses ISO timestamps (from user input or Canvas API responses) and converts
them to Canvas-compatible UTC ISO format ending with 'Z'.
The function handles various input types: datetime objects, date objects, Arrow
objects, and ISO timestamp strings.
All input times are interpreted in the system's local timezone and converted to
UTC.


